title: Pecan Pie Cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, and melted butter until well blended. Reserve 2/3 cup of this batter.
Spray a 9x13 pan with cooking spray. Spread remaining batter into this pan and bake at 325 for 15 minutes, or until just lightly browned.
In a mixing bowl, stir together reserved 2/3 cup batter, syrup, 3 eggs, brown sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Pour filling on top of crust and cook at 325 for 50-60 minutes, until set in the center.
Allow to cool completely before serving.
ingredients: 1 box yellow cake or butter cake mix
1/2 cup melted butter (or margarine, I don’t judge)
